ğŸ“Œ This tells MySQL that you want to work inside the BookStore database.

âœ… 3. Create a Table
Letâ€™s create a Books table with 5 columns: id, title, author, genre, and price.

CREATE TABLE Books (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    title VARCHAR(100),
    author VARCHAR(100),
    genre VARCHAR(50),
    price DECIMAL(6,2)
);
ğŸ“Œ Explanation of columns:
id: Auto-incrementing integer, primary key
title: Book title (up to 100 characters)
author: Authorâ€™s name (up to 100 characters)
genre: Type of book (e.g., Fiction, Non-fiction)
price: Decimal with up to 6 digits, 2 after the decimal point (e.g., 999.99)

âœ… 4. Insert Data into the Table
