After the above operations, youâ€™ll see:

| id | title      | author         | genre       | price  |
| -- | ---------- | -------------- | ----------- | ------ |
| 1  | Clean Code | Robert Martin  | Programming | 450.00 |
| 2  | The Hobbit | J.R.R. Tolkien | Fantasy     | 350.00 |

âœ… 9. Filtering with WHERE
To show only books with a price greater than 400:

SELECT * FROM Books
WHERE price > 400;

âœ… 10. Filtering with LIKE
To find books where the title starts with "C":

SELECT * FROM Books
WHERE title LIKE 'C%';
ğŸ“Œ % is a wildcard:
'C%' â†’ starts with C
'%e' â†’ ends with e
'%Code%' â†’ contains â€œCodeâ€

âœ… 11. Filtering with BETWEEN
To get books priced between 300 and 500:

SELECT * FROM Books
WHERE price BETWEEN 300 AND 500;

âœ… Combine Filters
To find programming books priced below 500:

SELECT * FROM Books
WHERE genre = 'Programming' AND price < 500;

âœ… 12. Sorting Data with ORDER BY
ğŸ”¹ Sort books by price (lowest to highest):
